# CopyPageButton

A button that copies the current page content as text to the clipboard. Placed below the page title on every API page.

## Properties

This component takes no props. It derives the `.md` URL from the current page pathname.

## Behavior

| Step | Action |
|------|--------|
| Mouseenter | Begins fetching the `.md` version of the page from `docs.datadoghq.com` |
| Click | Copies the fetched text (or DOM-extracted fallback) to clipboard |
| After copy | Shows "Copied!" with a checkmark icon for 3 seconds |
| Cache | Results are cached per URL to avoid redundant fetches |

## Fallback

If the `.md` fetch fails (e.g. during local development), the component extracts text from the DOM by walking the `.prose` content area. It converts headings to markdown `#` format, links to `[text](url)` format, and preserves block structure.

## Visual states

The button has two visual states:

- **Default**: clipboard icon + "Copy page"
- **Copied**: clipboard-with-checkmark icon + "Copied" (resets after 3 seconds)

Both label strings render at all times — the inactive one is hidden with `visibility: hidden` so the button keeps a constant width. The icon stays in place when the label flips between states.

## Usage

The component is used directly in API page templates with `client:idle` hydration:

```astro
<CopyPageButton client:idle />
```

It appears on all API pages: the index, category pages, individual operation pages, and static pages (rate limits, scopes, using the API).
